---
import DefaultLayout from '@layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import PageHeader from '@components/PageHeader.astro'
---

<DefaultLayout title="Resume">
  <PageHeader
    title="Resumé"
    subtitle="Bryson Best - Full Stack Developer"
    bgType="bordered"
  />
  <section class="narrow container my-16">
    <div class="space-content">
      <h3 class="mt-8 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Highlights of Qualifications</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-8">
        <li>Technical experience in multiple programming languages and frameworks, including HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, Python, SQL, MongoDB, Kubernetes, Node.js, Express.js, Vue.js, and React.js.</li>
        <li>Comfortable working with PERN (PostgreSQL, Express, React.js, Node.js) and MEVN (MongoDB, Express.js, Vue.js, and Node.js) stacks.</li>
        <li>Extensive experience managing policy projects and their components.</li>
        <li>Managing and collaborating in real time and asynchronously with large distributed teams.</li>
        <li>Extensive experience in case management, project management, and the delivery of formal decisions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="mt-8 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Work Experience</h3>
      <div class="resume-section">
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Full Stack Developer</span>
            <span class="font-light">Ministry of Social Development and Poverty Reduction, Victoria BC</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">May 2024 - Present</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Work within Agile sprints in a cross‑functional team to plan, build, and ship new features on a cloud‑hosted platform.</li>
            <li>Develop responsive, component‑based front‑end interfaces using React.js and TypeScript.</li>
            <li>Build and maintain CI/CD pipelines.</li>
            <li>Ensure reliability and scalability of applications through rigorous testing.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Full Stack Developer</span>
            <span>Public Service Agency, Victoria BC</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">April 2022 - May 2024</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Research, design, and code novel features for existing web programs.</li>
            <li>Collaborate with stakeholders and end‑users to iterate on feature designs.</li>
            <li>Develop and deploy new custom web and desktop applications.</li>
            <li>Provide hands‑on user support and training sessions.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Policy Analyst</span>
            <span>Ministry of Social Development and Poverty Reduction, Victoria BC</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">July 2019 - April 2022</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Provide in-depth analysis of legislation, policy, and legal issues, including implications, alternatives, and recommendations.</li>
            <li>Analyze datasets and social policy information utilizing automation tools built with Python.</li>
            <li>Support case-management software development through ensuring program adherence to policy, legislation, and accessibility requirements.</li>
            <li>Manage policy projects related to the provincial income and disability assistance programs.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Health Assistance Adjudicator</span>
            <span> Ministry of Social Development and Poverty Reduction, Vancouver BC</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">September 2016 - July 2019</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Researched and comprehensively examined medical evidence, reports, and related documentation to determine eligibility for health supplements and the Persons with Disabilities designation.</li>
            <li>Prepared comprehensive written summaries justifying adjudication decisions.</li>
            <li>Managed projects related to disability and medical equipment processes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Employment and Assistance Worker</span>
            <span> Ministry of Social Development and Poverty Reduction, Vancouver, BC</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">May 2014 - September 2016</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Managed the disability and income assistance cases of a large volume of clients.</li>
            <li>Applied legislation and policy in daily adjudication of client requests, and defended these decisions with detailed written documentation.</li>
            <li>Assessed clients with individually unique employment plans focused on helping them get back to work.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Research Assistant</span>
            <span>University of the Fraser Valley, Abbotsford BC</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">September 2012 - April 2014</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Responsible for the development and execution of various experimental research on psychological performance.</li>
            <li>Used HTML, CSS, and Javascript in front-end development of websites for research and presentation purposes.</li>
            <li>Utilized SPSS to analyze research data stored in detailed database files.</li>
            <li>Collaborated with a team of specialists in different fields, in order to research various psychological and social phenomena and conduct further analysis.</li>
            <li>Managed individual project components for team - monitoring progress and statistics towards completion.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="mt-8 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Volunteer Experience</h3>
      <div class="resume-section">
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Independent Open-Source Contributor</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">February 2020 - Present</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Utilize various programming languages to develop full-stack web-applications.</li>
            <li>Submit pull requests to open-source web applications.</li>
            <li>Experience in programming using HTML5, CSS, SASS, Bootstrap, JavaScript, jQuery, NodeJS, Express.JS and React.JS.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Group Facilitator</span>
            <span>Health Initiative for Men, Surrey, BC</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">Oct 2015 - April 2017</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Worked with a team of co-facilitators to plan and organize group activities for self-expression and learning.</li>
            <li>Collaborated to develop and manage new projects for social inclusion and social media outreach campaigns.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="mt-8 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Education & Certification</h3>
      <div class="resume-section">
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Diploma in Web Development</span>
            <span> Lighthouse Labs</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">May 2022</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Bachelor of Arts Degree</span>
            <span> University of the Fraser Valley</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">April 2014</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="resume-job">
          <div class="resume-job-header flex-col">
            <span class="font-bold">Diploma in Disability and Rehabilitation Management</span>
            <span> Simon Fraser University</span>
            <span class="float-right font-mono text-sm">April 2017</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style lang="scss">
    .resume-section {
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }
    .resume-job {
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .resume-job-header {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: baseline;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    ul {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    @media (min-width: 600px) {
      .resume-job-header {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</DefaultLayout>
